 WHITE PAPER

ABSTRACT
 In product versions earlier than IBM® Content Manager OnDemand V8.4.1, administrators were required to grant full Oracle® DBA authority to the Content Manager OnDemand instance owner. In Content Manager OnDemand V8.4.1 and V8.5.0, clients can now use a reduced set of privileges.

Content Manager OnDemand is typically installed with the Content Manager OnDemand instance owner having full DBA privileges. In Oracle environments, some clients want to install Content Manager OnDemand with a reduced set of database privileges to meet their own corporate guidelines. 

CONTENT
Content Manager OnDemand can be installed, configured, and run in an Oracle 10g or later environment using a reduced set of database privileges. This article addresses the required privileges. Note that further DBA privileges might be required depending on the client's environment and future Content Manager OnDemand product fixes or enhancements.


Administrators can use the Oracle SQLPLUS utility to perform the following steps.

1. Create the Content Manager OnDemand instance owner as a regular user. (See the Oracle Configuration Notes from the Content Manager OnDemand for Multiplatforms Installation and Configuration Guide.)

2. Create the ONDEMAND role. The required privileges for a Content Manager OnDemand instance owner are grouped into this ONDEMAND role. To create the ONDEMAND role, from the SQLPLUS utility, run the attached SQL script, ora_create_ondemand_role.sql,as follows: 

 * SQL> @ora_create_ondemand_role.sql 

ora_create_ondemand_role.sql [/support/docview.wss?uid=swg27015003&aid=2]ora_create_ondemand_role.sql [/support/docview.wss?uid=swg27015003&aid=1] 


3. If the Content Manager OnDemand instance owner is already defined and currently has the DBA role, the DBA role should be removed using command:  * SQL> REVOKE DBA FROM <od_owner>;


4. Grant the ONDEMAND role to the Content Manager OnDemand instance owner: 

 * SQL> GRANT ONDEMAND TO <od_owner>;


5. Grant to the Content Manager OnDemand instance owner an unlimited amount of any table space in the database:  * SQL> GRANT UNLIMITED TABLESPACE TO <od_owner>;


This set of steps will provide the Content Manager OnDemand instance owner with the minimum set of privileges required to perform Oracle database tasks to manage the Content Manager OnDemand database. 

The following code sample lists the contents of the attachment ora_create_ondemand_role.sql: 

---------------------------------------------------------------------- 
-- Create ONDEMAND role for Content Manager OnDemand instance owner 
-- 
-- Notes: 
-- SQL> @ora_create_ondemand_role.sql 
-- SQL> CREATE USER <od_owner> IDENTIFIED BY ora_od_password 
-- SQL> GRANT ONDEMAND TO <od_owner>; 
-- SQL> GRANT UNLIMITED TABLESPACE TO <od_owner>; 
-- 
---------------------------------------------------------------------- 

-- 
-- Create Content Manager OnDemand role : ONDEMAND 
-- 
DROP ROLE ONDEMAND; 
CREATE ROLE ONDEMAND; 


-- Database 
grant ALTER SYSTEM to ONDEMAND; 
grant SELECT ANY DICTIONARY to ONDEMAND; 

-- Session 
grant CREATE SESSION to ONDEMAND; 

-- Tablespaces 
grant CREATE TABLESPACE to ONDEMAND; 
grant DROP TABLESPACE to ONDEMAND; 

-- Tables 
grant ALTER ANY TABLE to ONDEMAND; 
grant BACKUP ANY TABLE to ONDEMAND; 
grant CREATE TABLE to ONDEMAND; 
grant DELETE ANY TABLE to ONDEMAND; 
grant DROP ANY TABLE to ONDEMAND; 
grant INSERT ANY TABLE to ONDEMAND; 
grant LOCK ANY TABLE to ONDEMAND; 
grant SELECT ANY TABLE to ONDEMAND; 
grant UPDATE ANY TABLE to ONDEMAND; 

-- Indexes 
grant CREATE ANY INDEX to ONDEMAND; 
grant DROP ANY INDEX to ONDEMAND; 

